<br>
The lifetap on the bonedancer is instant so you cant interupt with snare.<br>
<br>
I have tried mezzing the commander, but this didnt stop the other pets from healing. <br>
<br>
If you mez the bonedancer and charge the pets, the healing pets kite you.  I also can not &quot;one shot&quot; the healer pet when I do catch up to it.   The pets are tougher if the bd summons only 3 pets vs. 4 pets.   If just summons 3 pets the healers will be green instead of gray.  You must of fought a bd who is inexperienced.<br>
<br>
Regarding your post, have you actually beaten a level 50 supp bd who knows how to play their class recently or are your suggestions just theory?<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->         <br>
<br>
I think you probably you fought a bd who had 4 pets up, 2 healers that were grey.  Not a very good setup for a bd that is fighting someone.<br>
<br>
P.S. I have also tried to damage the pets with a dd so they start to heal the pets before the bonedancer, but that doesnt stop them from healing the bonedancer for long.  Plus the bonedancer will nuke you while you are playing with pets after our short mez wears off.  <br>
<br>
If you have any other ideas, I would be interested in hearing them.  There is a certain bonedancer in my guild that I would like to pummel.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->        <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.dravness.com/x.daoc/sig-sing.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=singdemsong>Singdemsong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://camelot.dragonzones.com/sig/ns.jpg " BORDER=0> at: 10/21/03 6:54 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ff0000>- </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald>Team Skald</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1>General Discussion</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font> <!-- #EndEditable -->
